      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal concept that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe on basic liberties even if it follows proper legal procedures. It has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and bodily integrity. This doctrine allows courts to protect deeply rooted rights, like those concerning marriage and personal decisions, against legislative interference. Therefore, it serves as a vital bulwark for individual freedom against arbitrary state power.",
